WEBVTT

00:32.770 --> 00:33.951
Brave the Cold?

00:36.934 --> 00:43.780
Well, recently we had a little bit of an issue with a door in our house.

00:43.860 --> 00:50.206
It was the door that enters and exits from our family room to our garage.

00:51.828 --> 00:54.150
And it just wouldn't work quite right.

00:55.091 --> 00:56.492
It wouldn't close the way it should.

00:56.532 --> 01:02.418
And no matter how much I tried to adjust it, something fell off.

01:03.074 --> 01:04.075
I got a picture here.

01:05.256 --> 01:08.980
You can see where the latch is hitting the plate.

01:09.881 --> 01:10.862
Just a little low.

01:12.744 --> 01:20.131
Now, the only reason I can say that confidently is because someone smarter than I am at this stuff told me that was what the problem was.

01:21.593 --> 01:30.802
So, like basically the door would not latch and like if I would open the garage and a cold like air would come in it would just blow right open.

01:31.266 --> 01:40.676
which in addition to letting cold in the house, when you have a one-year-old dog that likes to run everywhere, it's not ideal to keep the dog in the house.

01:40.936 --> 01:42.858
So it was not something we wanted to let go.

01:43.319 --> 01:45.201
So I did what most of us nowadays do.

01:45.221 --> 01:47.243
I got on YouTube.

01:49.105 --> 01:52.829
And I found a few tutorial videos.

01:53.610 --> 02:01.138
I watched as the people confidently explained three easy steps to explain how to fix this very, very common problem.

02:02.242 --> 02:04.845
And I immediately realized I was in over my head.

02:07.007 --> 02:09.209
The terminology they were using was unfamiliar.

02:09.369 --> 02:11.691
I kept pausing the video to look up words.

02:13.393 --> 02:15.515
You know the saying goes, it's Greek to me.

02:15.555 --> 02:23.623
I'm a Bible nerd, so like ancient Greek isn't always Greek to me, but like door stuff is Greek to me.

02:24.343 --> 02:31.250
So, you know, I had to look up stuff and I eventually, I just stopped trying to understand it all together.

02:31.650 --> 02:34.534
And I just started to try to copy what I was seeing them do.

02:35.055 --> 02:41.686
So if they took a screwdriver and a hammer and pounded on the screwdriver to try to move something, I tried to do it.

02:42.126 --> 02:45.011
And then I'd close the door and it wouldn't latch.

02:47.274 --> 02:48.396
I tightened what they tightened.

02:48.416 --> 02:49.998
I adjusted what they adjusted.

02:50.018 --> 02:54.425
I tried to mimic the motions of the video, but it didn't fix the problem.

02:55.587 --> 03:00.114
So I finally called a fix it guy who actually knew what he was doing.

03:01.442 --> 03:08.569
And when the, when the fix the guy showed up, it became obvious pretty quickly that this wasn't his first time dealing with something like this.

03:09.150 --> 03:11.172
He knew exactly which tools to use.

03:11.512 --> 03:14.536
He knew the common issues before he even took the door apart.

03:14.796 --> 03:19.681
And yes, he had to pull the frame off, which was something I never would have done because I would have cracked the frame.

03:19.841 --> 03:20.882
I promise you that.

03:22.584 --> 03:25.387
He diagnosed the problem almost immediately and got to work.

03:26.808 --> 03:28.370
Now here's what struck me the most.

03:28.834 --> 03:35.442
As he worked, I was in the room because I like to try to learn something, even though I wasn't understanding the YouTubers out there.

03:36.103 --> 03:46.696
And as he was working, he was explaining what was wrong, not with technical jargon, not to impress me with his years of experience and knowledge, but in language I could actually understand.

03:46.756 --> 03:53.184
He showed me what I had missed and why my attempts to fix the door didn't work and what needed to change.

03:54.145 --> 03:54.746
And he fixed it.

03:55.727 --> 03:56.348
And guess what?

03:56.368 --> 03:58.130
The door stays shut.

03:59.202 --> 04:00.103
It's really nice.

04:01.344 --> 04:02.045
Merry Christmas.

04:04.627 --> 04:07.890
And I walked away understanding something that I hadn't before.

04:07.910 --> 04:12.575
If we're honest, most of us have moments like I just described.

04:13.155 --> 04:17.420
We work really hard, we try our best, but we still miss what actually helps.

04:19.221 --> 04:24.166
And that experience is sticking with me because it reminded me of something simple but important.

04:24.947 --> 04:28.370
Clarity doesn't just fix problems, it helps people.

04:29.698 --> 04:40.254
Or as Brene Brown likes to say, and as our missions team has in every meeting on the top of our agenda, clarity is kindness.

04:42.317 --> 04:44.641
Good intentions aren't enough.

04:45.362 --> 04:46.384
Effort isn't enough.

04:46.504 --> 04:48.126
Even passion isn't enough.

04:48.367 --> 04:53.234
If you don't understand what's actually happening, you can work hard and still miss the point.

04:55.618 --> 05:02.228
And that's exactly the issue that Paul's addressing in the chapter that we're gonna be reading this morning in 1 Corinthians 14.

05:02.268 --> 05:12.122
Again, he's writing to a church that is passionate, expressive, and very, very spiritually active, but not always helpful.

05:13.484 --> 05:20.674
People are speaking, people are participating, but clarity is missing when the church gathers in Corinth.

05:21.536 --> 05:23.218
And because clarity is missing,

05:23.522 --> 05:27.106
The church isn't being built up the way it should be.

05:27.807 --> 05:32.053
So Paul reframes the whole conversation with one guiding principle.

05:32.914 --> 05:39.962
The spirit works to build others up, not to show ourselves off.

05:41.925 --> 05:52.498
The truth reshapes how spiritual gifts are used, how worship functions, and even how believers interact with people who don't yet.

05:52.930 --> 05:53.471
believe.

05:55.453 --> 06:06.307
So I want us to step into Paul's argument together this morning, beginning where he starts with a reminder that clarity and edification are not optional in the life of the church.

06:07.028 --> 06:13.216
They are expressions of love, which is what he talked about last week when we read 1 Corinthians 13.

06:15.219 --> 06:20.946
And we see clearly in first, we see that the most clearly in 1 Corinthians 14 verse 6, so I want to start

06:21.506 --> 06:22.748
there this morning.

06:22.948 --> 06:25.951
Because Paul isn't correcting a church that lacks passion.

06:26.512 --> 06:30.076
He's correcting a church that lacks direction.

06:30.857 --> 06:37.505
And Paul's goal isn't to quiet the spirit, but to make sure the spirit's work actually reaches people.

06:38.787 --> 06:41.190
The Corinthians loved spiritual experiences.

06:41.510 --> 06:43.693
They loved expressive worship.

06:43.713 --> 06:45.615
They loved exercising their gifts.

06:45.996 --> 06:48.058
But Paul's concern is simple in searching.

06:48.819 --> 06:51.282
Are the things you're doing actually helping anyone?

06:52.546 --> 06:59.395
So before he gives practical instructions, Paul lays down a principle that governs everything that follows.

06:59.856 --> 07:05.343
And he does it by reframing how spiritual gifts are meant to function in the first place.

07:06.084 --> 07:08.528
Paul's argument moves in three movements.

07:09.529 --> 07:11.752
One, clarity builds the church.

07:12.133 --> 07:16.238
Two, clarity serves outsiders, and three, clarity reflects Christ.

07:17.019 --> 07:22.066
So I want us to read this first passage here as he brings the first movement, starting in verse six.

07:22.338 --> 07:23.299
of chapter 14.

07:24.681 --> 07:35.736
So now brothers and sisters, if I come to you speaking in tongues, how will I benefit you unless I speak to you with a revelation or knowledge or prophecy or teaching?

07:36.718 --> 07:48.754
Even lifeless instruments that produce sounds, whether flute or harp, if they don't make a distinction in the notes, how will what is played on the flute or harp be recognized?

07:49.378 --> 07:54.863
In fact, if the bugle makes an unclear sound, who will prepare for battle?

07:56.024 --> 08:02.711
In the same way, unless you use your tongue for intelligible speech, how will what is spoken be known?

08:03.151 --> 08:05.253
For you will be speaking into the air.

08:05.914 --> 08:08.756
There are doubtless many different kinds of languages in the world.

08:08.816 --> 08:11.019
None is without meaning.

08:11.459 --> 08:18.866
Therefore, if I do not know the meaning of the language, I will be a foreigner to the speaker, and the speaker will be a foreigner to me.

08:19.138 --> 08:27.226
So also you, since you are zealous for spiritual gifts, seek to excel in building up the church.

08:28.707 --> 08:31.930
So in verses six through eight here, Paul begins with a simple question.

08:32.771 --> 08:39.097
If I come to you speaking in tongues, he says, how will I benefit you unless I bring revelation, knowledge, prophecy, or teaching?

08:40.098 --> 08:42.680
His point is not to be anti-tongues.

08:43.361 --> 08:49.106
And as an aside, the word tongues really ought to be translated languages.

08:49.474 --> 09:04.430
The idea of the gift of speaking in tongues in the early church was that languages that were not known to the speaker were gifted them by the Spirit so that they could speak in another language and reach someone that speaks that language.

09:06.813 --> 09:08.595
It wasn't a bunch of gobble to you.

09:08.615 --> 09:10.957
Anyway, that settled.

09:12.639 --> 09:15.122
Paul uses everyday illustrations

09:15.202 --> 09:19.766
using musical instruments, battle trumpets to make one point unmistakable.

09:19.826 --> 09:21.948
Sound without meaning doesn't serve anybody.

09:22.949 --> 09:29.155
Spiritual activity that isn't understandable may feel powerful, but it doesn't accomplish God's purpose.

09:29.876 --> 09:32.378
So Paul is setting a tone in this first part.

09:32.779 --> 09:35.802
If it doesn't help people grow, it misses the point of the gift.

09:37.143 --> 09:39.505
It doesn't help people grow, it misses the point of the gift.

09:41.747 --> 09:44.530
In verses nine through 12, Paul sharpens the argument.

09:44.674 --> 09:48.900
He says, speaking words no one understands is like speaking into the air.

09:49.921 --> 09:53.646
Noise without impact, effort without bearing fruit.

09:54.367 --> 09:57.191
Then comes verse 12, which is one of our anchor verses today.

09:58.112 --> 10:03.640
Since you are eager for manifestations of the spirit, strive to excel in building up the church.

10:04.461 --> 10:08.326
Paul doesn't rebuke their eagerness, he redirects it.

10:09.628 --> 10:14.194
Spiritual maturity is not measured by how much you experience

10:14.562 --> 10:20.450
but by how much others are strengthened because of you and the gift you display.

10:20.510 --> 10:23.014
This is the first major framing.

10:23.034 --> 10:27.941
The spirit works to build up, not to show off.

10:29.162 --> 10:33.208
But Paul knows clarity isn't just about the room.

10:33.248 --> 10:35.712
It's also about the person using the gift.

10:35.992 --> 10:43.122
And so he goes on in verse 13 and he says, therefore the person who speaks in a tongue should pray that he can interpret.

10:43.682 --> 10:48.327
For if I pray in a tongue, my spirit prays, but my understanding is unfruitful.

10:49.188 --> 10:49.708
What then?

10:49.749 --> 10:53.993
I will pray with the spirit, and I will also pray with my understanding.

10:54.434 --> 10:59.379
I will sing praise with the spirit, and I will also sing praise with my understanding.

10:59.399 --> 11:04.344
Otherwise, if you praise with the spirit, how will the outsider say amen?

11:04.404 --> 11:09.810
At your giving of thanks, since he does not know what you are saying.

11:11.042 --> 11:14.928
For you may very well be giving thanks, but the other person is not being built up.

11:16.070 --> 11:18.814
I thank God that I speak in tongues more than all of you.

11:19.835 --> 11:30.631
Yet in the church, I would rather speak five words with my understanding in order to teach others also than 10,000 words in a tongue.

11:31.973 --> 11:34.637
So Paul turns it inward here in verses 13 through 15.

11:34.918 --> 11:40.466
He explains that uninterpreted tongues

11:40.706 --> 11:42.889
don't even benefit the speaker fully.

11:43.330 --> 11:46.455
It says, my spirit prays, but my mind is unfruitful.

11:46.915 --> 11:47.897
And that's critical here.

11:48.177 --> 11:54.927
Because Paul refuses this idea that spirituality requires abandoning understanding.

11:55.728 --> 12:00.596
True spiritual worship engages both the heart and the mind.

12:01.717 --> 12:04.882
The spirit does not override human responsibility.

12:05.058 --> 12:07.440
The speaker remains in control.

12:07.741 --> 12:11.044
The gift remains accountable to the goal of love.

12:12.346 --> 12:15.709
And this dismantles the idea that the spirit made me do it.

12:17.331 --> 12:23.778
Or that there's this lack of control because now Paul brings outsiders into view in verses 16 through 19.

12:24.338 --> 12:31.826
People that are outside the church, unbelievers that might be hearing what's going on and wondering how they might respond.

12:32.386 --> 12:40.278
If an unbeliever hears something that they can't understand, they can't agree, they can't learn, and they can't respond in faith.

12:43.122 --> 12:52.636
And so he says in verse 19, I would rather speak five understandable words to instruct others than 10,000 words in a tongue or language.

12:54.258 --> 12:56.782
And that's no exaggeration, it's Paul's conviction.

12:57.763 --> 12:59.666
Paul experienced grace

13:00.610 --> 13:05.876
that he knew he did not deserve and he wanted to spread it to the entire world over.

13:07.438 --> 13:16.568
It is his missionary work that brought the Corinthians to faith and he's wanting them to think in the same way as they think about those outside of their ranks.

13:17.169 --> 13:24.937
Paul values instruction over intensity, he understanding over spectacle and helpfulness over volume.

13:25.698 --> 13:29.202
Love asks, what will I actually move someone

13:29.314 --> 13:31.476
or what will actually move someone toward God.

13:34.219 --> 13:38.142
And then our last few verses here, we want to jump ahead to verse 23 here.

13:38.603 --> 13:49.753
Paul writes, if therefore the whole church assembles together and all are speaking in tongues, and people who are outsiders or unbelievers come in, will they not say that you are out of your minds?

13:51.235 --> 13:59.122
But if all are prophesying and someone believer or outsider comes in, he is convicted by all and is called to account by all.

13:59.842 --> 14:08.775
The secrets of his heart will be revealed, and as a result, he will fall face down and worship God, proclaiming God is really among you.

14:10.157 --> 14:18.470
What, then brothers and sisters, whenever you come together, each one has a hymn, a teaching, a revelation, a tongue, or an interpretation.

14:18.510 --> 14:24.178
Everything is to be done for building.

14:26.530 --> 14:29.753
So Paul here widens the lens for us further.

14:31.655 --> 14:34.037
He addresses maturity directly in these verses.

14:34.057 --> 14:39.783
He tells them to stop thinking like children, chasing what feels exciting instead of what is beneficial.

14:41.704 --> 14:43.266
Then he describes two outcomes.

14:43.987 --> 14:56.018
Chaotic unintelligible worship causes outsiders to say, you are out of your minds, yet clear intelligible proclamation leads outsiders to conviction, repentance, and worship.

14:57.698 --> 15:01.502
This is one of Paul's strongest evangelistic moments.

15:02.363 --> 15:04.965
Order and clarity don't stifle the spirit.

15:05.346 --> 15:08.249
They create space for transformation.

15:09.050 --> 15:14.495
And finally, Paul ends with verse 26, which is the anchor of this entire chapter.

15:15.876 --> 15:25.266
He says, when you come together, let all things be done for building up, whether you're building up your brother and sister in the faith,

15:26.018 --> 15:29.823
or you're building up someone who has not yet come to faith.

15:31.044 --> 15:38.494
It is a discipling strategy and an evangelistic strategy, which by the way, those two things ought not be separated.

15:39.415 --> 15:45.362
We are to reach the loss beyond these walls and build one another up in our walk with Jesus.

15:46.143 --> 15:47.425
Notice what Paul affirms.

15:47.885 --> 15:49.107
Everyone participates.

15:49.487 --> 15:50.629
Everyone contributes.

15:50.989 --> 15:54.834
Everyone submits their contribution to one purpose.

15:54.978 --> 15:57.480
The question is never did I express myself.

15:58.481 --> 16:02.305
The question is did the body grow stronger because I showed up.

16:04.748 --> 16:06.830
And this verse pulls the whole chapter together.

16:07.250 --> 16:11.254
Again, the spirit works to build up, not to show off.

16:12.315 --> 16:14.637
Not for attention, but transformation.

16:14.978 --> 16:23.666
If Paul's point is that the spirit builds people up rather than drawing attention to ourselves, then the question we all have to ask is not am I gifted

16:23.970 --> 16:25.412
But am I being helpful?

16:26.274 --> 16:28.838
Or am I a gift to others?

16:29.740 --> 16:34.107
And the best place to see what that looks like is not Corinth.

16:34.868 --> 16:35.650
It's Christ.

16:36.271 --> 16:41.940
Because Jesus is the clearest picture of spirit-filled life the world has ever seen.

16:43.182 --> 16:45.606
Jesus could have spoken in riddles all the time.

16:45.646 --> 16:50.194
He could have overwhelmed people with mystery, and he did at times.

16:50.978 --> 16:54.002
He could have flexed divine knowledge at every turn, but he didn't.

16:55.103 --> 17:01.310
When Jesus taught, people said he speaks as one having authority, not because he was confusing, but because he was clear.

17:01.991 --> 17:10.881
He used stories, he used everyday images, and he spoke in ordinary ways that people could grasp.

17:10.901 --> 17:13.264
Jesus never said, how can I sound impressive?

17:13.324 --> 17:16.327
He asked, how can I make the Father known?

17:16.367 --> 17:18.610
That was his goal.

17:18.914 --> 17:24.442
If the Son of God chose clarity over spectacle, then spirit-shaped love will do the same."

17:26.304 --> 17:27.406
So here's a question for us.

17:28.267 --> 17:32.193
Where might I be more concerned with being impressive than being helpful?

17:33.254 --> 17:35.778
Because Jesus didn't communicate the same way to everyone.

17:36.478 --> 17:47.634
With scholars he reasoned, with fishermen he used nets and water, with children he welcomed them, with the hurting he slowed down and cared, and with outsiders he explained

17:48.226 --> 17:48.947
patiently.

17:49.808 --> 17:51.069
That is love at work.

17:51.670 --> 17:59.780
Paul's argument here in 1 Corinthians 14 rests on the same principle that love adapts for the sake of others.

18:00.861 --> 18:06.127
So this week, that might mean to explain instead of assuming someone knows.

18:06.948 --> 18:09.732
It might mean slowing down instead of powering through.

18:09.752 --> 18:13.356
It might mean asking questions instead of making statements.

18:14.037 --> 18:14.898
It might choose

18:15.010 --> 18:19.535
It might mean choosing words that serve rather than words that perform.

18:20.856 --> 18:22.939
Clarity isn't dumbing things down either.

18:23.559 --> 18:26.022
It's loving people enough to meet them where they're at.

18:28.044 --> 18:38.776
And one of Paul's biggest concerns in Corinth is that spiritual gifts were being used to elevate the individual rather than to strengthen the church body and community at large.

18:39.677 --> 18:41.499
But Jesus shows us a different way.

18:42.199 --> 18:44.722
Every miracle pointed away from himself

18:44.866 --> 18:46.388
and toward the glory of God.

18:46.448 --> 18:49.592
Every act of power was an act of service.

18:50.393 --> 18:54.018
Every moment of authority was shaped by humility.

18:54.819 --> 18:57.723
Jesus did not use the spirit to draw a crowd.

18:57.763 --> 19:01.347
He followed the lead of the spirit to restore people.

19:02.429 --> 19:09.618
So a spirit shaped life asks the question, is what I'm doing drawing attention to me or is it quietly building someone else?

19:12.898 --> 19:17.743
Paul repeatedly brings outsiders into the conversation in 1 Corinthians 14.

19:18.164 --> 19:19.045
Why would he do that?

19:19.706 --> 19:23.710
Because love is always aware of who is in the room and who is not.

19:24.951 --> 19:26.133
And Jesus did the same.

19:26.173 --> 19:29.777
Task collectors understood him and followed him.

19:30.638 --> 19:36.705
Sinners felt safe around him, inviting them into their home.

19:36.745 --> 19:41.650
Those on the margins leaned in, they didn't back away from Jesus.

19:42.114 --> 19:47.140
Not because he watered down the truth, but because he communicated it clearly and compassionately.

19:47.901 --> 19:49.223
So this ought to challenge us.

19:49.964 --> 20:02.679
In our conversations at our workplaces, within our families, amongst our church, are we creating clarity that invites people closer to Jesus or confusion that pushes them away?

20:04.622 --> 20:11.250
Five clear words that point to Christ will always matter more than 10,000 words.

20:11.618 --> 20:13.460
that leave people lost.

20:15.463 --> 20:19.528
This isn't just about church gatherings, this is also about everyday discipleship.

20:20.409 --> 20:36.088
It looks like speaking clearly instead of vaguely, listening before responding, explaining expectations rather than assuming them, offering encouragement people can actually act on, and sharing faith simply, not impressively.

20:36.529 --> 20:39.352
Because love doesn't ask, what do I want to express?

20:39.713 --> 20:40.594
Love asks,

20:40.738 --> 20:43.302
What will help you grow?

20:44.764 --> 20:47.688
And that's the heartbeat of Christ.

20:48.489 --> 20:59.886
Paul is not asking the Corinthians or us to stop using our gifts, our talent, our time, our resources, but he's asking us to submit to love.

21:00.808 --> 21:07.518
And love looks like Jesus, clear, humble, helpful, others centered.

21:07.578 --> 21:10.482
So here's the question to carry with us this week.

21:10.882 --> 21:15.167
Where might the Spirit be inviting me to choose clarity as an act of love?

21:16.048 --> 21:19.492
In my relationships, no matter where God has placed me.

21:21.315 --> 21:27.782
This week, choose one conversation where you'll slow down, explain more clearly, and aim to help rather than impress.

21:28.323 --> 21:35.692
Not to show off, not to draw attention to oneself, but to quietly, faithfully build someone else up.

21:36.853 --> 21:38.796
Because the Spirit works to build up.

21:39.216 --> 21:40.658
And when we follow Jesus,

21:40.898 --> 21:43.222
we learn to do the same.

21:44.083 --> 21:52.976
The same Jesus who spoke clearly lived humbly and gave his life for us now invites us to live the same kind of love by his spirit.

21:54.559 --> 22:01.309
One of the things that I love about Matthew's telling of the Christmas story is how understated it is.

22:03.512 --> 22:06.397
There are no angels singing in the sky like in Luke.

22:07.518 --> 22:09.842
No shepherds rushing to a field

22:10.786 --> 22:13.711
No extended dialogue.

22:13.731 --> 22:27.032
Just this quiet, weighty moment where an angel appears to Joseph in a dream and says in essence, here's what's happening, here's what God is doing, and here's what you need to do next.

22:28.354 --> 22:32.461
I love this picture here of Joseph and the angel, it's a classic painting.

22:32.862 --> 22:35.386
It looks like the angel slapped Joseph and knocked him out.

22:36.547 --> 22:38.130
Maybe trying to get his attention

22:38.530 --> 22:39.551
sleeping too deeply.

22:39.651 --> 22:41.172
I got something to say to you anyway.

22:43.194 --> 22:47.178
So Joseph is in a moment here confused.

22:48.419 --> 22:50.421
His life has been flipped upside down.

22:50.481 --> 22:55.606
Nothing about his situation makes any sense.

22:57.207 --> 23:08.498
He's discovered that his betrothed is pregnant and has a pretty lofty claim that this was God orchestrated.

23:11.042 --> 23:15.808
And he tries to make the righteous move and divorce her quietly.

23:15.868 --> 23:19.452
But the angel visits him in a dream.

23:21.375 --> 23:23.297
And God doesn't overwhelm him with mystery.

23:23.317 --> 23:25.540
He doesn't give him riddles when the angel appears.

23:25.740 --> 23:28.243
He doesn't ask him to figure it out on his own.

23:28.303 --> 23:31.867
God speaks very clearly in the story.

23:32.128 --> 23:34.390
And Matthew 1, 23, 21, it says this.

23:34.410 --> 23:37.394
This is, but after he had considered these things,

23:37.506 --> 23:49.921
This move an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream saying, Joseph, son of David, don't be afraid to take Mary as your wife because what has been conceived in her is from the Holy Spirit.

23:50.742 --> 24:00.154
She will give birth to a son and you are to name him Jesus because he will save his people from their sins.

24:01.656 --> 24:03.698
That is clarity.

24:04.514 --> 24:15.685
When Joseph's life didn't feel all that clear, God intervened with a very clear message, miraculous indeed, but clear.

24:15.705 --> 24:20.269
It was not clarity for a spectacle.

24:20.769 --> 24:22.972
It was clarity so that Joseph could be obedient.

24:23.632 --> 24:34.002
It was clarity that built up Joseph's faith in God and clarity that moved him forward in trust that he could do as God commanded him to do

24:34.146 --> 24:38.192
even when the situation had previously not made any sense.

24:39.593 --> 24:45.081
As though Joseph responds, not with applause, not with attention, but with quiet faithfulness.

24:46.343 --> 24:52.371
He gets up, he does what the angel says, and he steps into God's plan.

24:53.112 --> 24:56.857
That's the kind of clarity Christmas brought into the world.

24:58.039 --> 25:00.602
God didn't send Jesus to impress humanity.

25:01.003 --> 25:03.506
He sent him to save humanity.

25:04.258 --> 25:06.961
That's the clear message Joseph received.

25:07.481 --> 25:11.585
That's the message that Paul came through faith receiving.

25:12.126 --> 25:19.793
And that's the message that he wants to clearly communicate to the Corinthians so that they can communicate it to others.

25:21.635 --> 25:24.338
He didn't arrive in a way that showed off divine power.

25:24.718 --> 25:32.946
He came in a way that could be understood, received and trusted, which means Christmas itself as a living picture

25:33.282 --> 25:36.046
of Paul's point in 1 Corinthians 14.

25:36.567 --> 25:38.209
The spirit doesn't work to show off.

25:38.629 --> 25:40.552
The spirit works to build up.

25:42.114 --> 25:43.877
God speaks so people can follow.

25:44.297 --> 25:46.320
God acts so that people can trust.

25:46.680 --> 25:49.544
God draws near so people can live differently.

25:50.025 --> 25:55.312
So as we leave today, the question is not, how spiritual do I sound?

25:56.514 --> 25:58.997
Or how impressive is my faith?

26:00.179 --> 26:02.482
The question is, is my life helping others?

26:02.786 --> 26:05.090
take their next step toward Jesus.

26:06.271 --> 26:22.136
Because the same spirit who spoke clearly to Joseph, the same spirit who brought Christ into the world, the same spirit Paul writes about in Corinth, is still at work today in you and I.

26:23.218 --> 26:30.770
Not to confuse, not to compete, not to draw attention to ourselves, but to build people up.

26:31.234 --> 26:36.321
to make Jesus known and to invite a weary world into hope.

26:38.844 --> 26:40.967
That's Christmas and Corinth.

26:42.449 --> 26:45.232
And that's the work of the Spirit among us now.

26:46.674 --> 26:51.580
Because the Spirit works to build up, not to show off.

26:52.502 --> 26:55.986
I hope on your way in this morning you got a communion packet

26:59.586 --> 27:12.085
We take communion each Sunday as a body of believers when we come together because we fulfill the commandment that Jesus gave His earliest disciples to do this in remembrance of me.

27:13.147 --> 27:19.717
Jesus broke bread and He gave it to His disciples on the night He was betrayed and said, take and eat.

27:19.777 --> 27:21.580
This is my body which is given for you.

27:21.600 --> 27:25.666
And then He passed the cup and said, take and drink.

27:25.746 --> 27:28.050
This is my blood which is given for you.

27:29.378 --> 27:42.174
And when we take this act of obedience, this act of clarity of what God has done for us, we proclaim our faith in Him.

27:43.836 --> 27:58.354
We proclaim that we have received the gospel, that we have faithfully responded to it, and that we choose daily to faithfully live it out as a light

27:58.754 --> 28:00.617
and assault to others.

28:01.719 --> 28:14.322
So I invite you to take a moment to contemplate the goodness of God, the clear message of salvation that we've received, and after we take that moment of reflection, we'll take communion together as one church family.

29:02.306 --> 29:05.850
invite each and every one of you to take the bread from this cup and eat.

29:06.390 --> 29:08.352
This is his body, which is given for us.

29:16.400 --> 29:18.742
And likewise, I invite you to take and drink from this cup.

29:18.762 --> 29:25.169
This is his blood, which is poured out for us.

29:29.773 --> 29:30.674
Please pray with me.

29:33.154 --> 29:57.778
Dear Lord God, we thank you that we can hear the words that Paul wrote to the Corinthians who were so impassioned and boldened to try to live faithfully and spiritually but had things of it crossed up at times and we are often in the same spot.

29:58.819 --> 30:02.482
But I thank you for the boldness

30:02.914 --> 30:22.878
of your grace, the wonder of your mercy, the move that you made to send your son Jesus as we celebrated this time of year, his arrival, but even more so that he was obedient to you in giving of his life so that we could have life to the full.

30:22.898 --> 30:29.906
I thank you for that gospel message, and I pray that each and every one of us that are followers of your son Jesus

30:30.786 --> 30:41.380
will aim to live and to love with clarity, not only to one another to build each other up in faith, but to be a light to the world around us.

30:42.401 --> 30:47.247
The people that don't yet have faith haven't yet made that decision.

30:48.248 --> 30:58.962
And if someone in this room is at that point where they're wondering what it looks like to follow Jesus fully

30:59.650 --> 31:09.307
I pray that you will stir in their hearts the decision to be baptized and to follow in his footsteps.

31:11.351 --> 31:16.080
We thank you so much for being good to us and it's in your son Jesus name that we pray.

31:16.120 --> 31:17.362
Amen.

